  "system": {
    "description": "<p>When you cast a Spell that requires <strong>MP </strong>(through a base cost,&nbsp;Spell Enhancements, or both), you can attempt to cast the&nbsp;Spell without spending any <strong>MP</strong>.</p>\n<p>The total <strong>MP </strong>cost for the Spell must be equal to or lower than your <strong>Mana Spend Limit</strong>.</p>\n<p>Make a <strong>Spell Check</strong>. The <strong>DC </strong>equals 10 + the amount of <strong>MP&nbsp;</strong>you would normally spend to cast the Spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Success: </strong>The Spell takes effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure:</strong> The Spell fails.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spell Fatigue</span></p>\n<p>After the Spell succeeds or fails, the following effects&nbsp;immediately take place:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You gain <strong>Exhaustion 1</strong> which can&rsquo;t be removed by any&nbsp;means other than completing a <strong>Long Rest </strong>or the effect of&nbsp;the <strong>Wish Spell</strong>.</li>\n<li>You must roll on the <strong>Wild Magic</strong> <strong>Table</strong>. If an effect forces&nbsp;a creature to make a Save, it makes it against your <strong>Save DC</strong>.&nbsp;The effect from the table lasts until the end of your next&nbsp;turn.</li>\n</ul>",
